title: Median age of the population in Saudi Arabia 2015
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Age median in years. In total the number of data points it has is 21.
In general Age median in years has rose over the Year.
Age median in years is roughly constant from 1950 to 1995, and finally slightly increasing from 1995 to 2050.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2010 and 2015.
Maximum Age median in years, about 40.2 was reported at Year 2050
Minimum Age median in years about 18.0 was reached at Year 1970, and 1975
